ously in order to have more liquor available to make adjustments with. Therefore, that single malt you are sipping on has most likely been blended with different batches from the distillery. Single malt distillers are at a much greater disadvantage from blended whiskey makers when it comes to creating an undiscernible product. <br>";s:7:"keyword";s:30:"blended whiskey vs single malt";s:5:"links";s:4288:"<a href='https://www.pathshala.co/forum/page.php?id=d7382a-'></a>,
